Wash and dry produce.

Thinly slice @tomato{1}(thinly sliced). Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{3%oz}(trimmed, peeled and cut into sticks like fries; ours were 3 inches long and 1⁄3 inch thick).

Pat @sous vide chopped chicken{8%oz} dry with #paper towels{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken; season lightly with @salt{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{}.

Wrap @flour tortillas{2} in damp #paper towels{}; microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}. Place tortillas on a clean work surface; divide @mixed greens{2%oz}, tomato, and chicken between tortillas. Drizzle with half the @buttermilk ranch dressing{3%oz}.

Fold bottom sides of each tortilla up over filling, then fold over left and right sides toward filling. Roll up tortillas, starting with filled sides, to form wraps.

Halve wraps on a diagonal. Divide wraps and carrot sticks between plates. Serve with remaining dressing on the side.